Important rule:

PriorityQueue does NOT store elements as a fully sorted list.
It stores them as a HEAP.

A heap only guarantees that the first element is the smallest, not that the whole list is sorted.

So internally it may look like:

        a
       / \
      c   b
     /
    d


                            III. LinkedList
1.single LinkedList

A Linked List is a way to store data in memeory using nodes
that are connected with pointer (links) instead of storing
them next to each other like arry ,

structure
         | next is a node or pointer a reference to next node in list
         |
  | the value store
  V      V
[data | next ] -> [data | next ] -> [data | next ] -> null

example 

10 -> 20 -> 30 -> 40 -> null

Node
 ├── data
 └── next (pointer to next node)
   
2.Doubly LinkedList

A Doubly Linked List is an improved version of a linked list.
still like LinkedList it have data and node but this time structure like this

null <- [data | prev | next] <-> [data | prev | next] <-> [data | prev | next] -> null

example:  10 <-> 20 <-> 30 <-> 40

Node
 ├── prev
 ├── data
 └── next

