                    VI. selection sort 

selection sort = search through an array and keep track of minimum 
value during iteration. at the end iteration, we swap variable. 

it use Quandratic time O(n^2)
small data set = okay 
large data set = bad 

ok how the selection sort work ?

it the same as bubble sort but this is have int min and int temp .

light [9, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 8, 6 ] heavy 

    int min []         int temp [] 

att first it scan for smallest nummber so :

light [9, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 8, 6 ] heavy 

    int min [9]         int temp [] # at start 9 was the smallest c
                                      cuz it the first one .
   than : 
             | ouh oh the next number is smaller than 9 it 1 so
             V it store the number 1 in int min  and than push 9 to int temp
   light [9, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 8, 6 ] heavy 

    int min [1]         int temp [9]    

    than it swap the position swap the int min to the array so: 

    
    light [ 1, , 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 8, 6 ] heavy 

    int min []         int temp [9]   than it put 9 back after 1 
                |
                V


    light [1, 9, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 8, 6 ] heavy 

    int min []         int temp []  


    the cycle contiune like this till the array value
    start from the light to heavy 

    light [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9 ] heavy  : like this and the selection sort complete;

